 {id:'q3gate', los:['3.1.2a','3.1.3a','3.3.5b','3.4.2b','3.5.3b'], map:'world4', name:'Topic 3 Gatekeeper', emoji:'🧭', c:6, r:5, lines:()=>[
   "Welcome to the PORTFOLIO CONSTRUCTION VILLAGE — Topic 3. This bridge now sits exactly where it belongs: between Asset Owners City and Risk Village.",
   "This village is built from the course AND your error log. Repeated traps are marked in dialogue: MVO optimizes WEIGHTS, efficient frontiers are for RISK-AVERSE investors, risk parity is NOT solved by MVO, constrained clones are not liquidity-based replication, and CPPI trades must be calculated step by step.",
   "Buildings: MVO Tower, Total Portfolio HQ, Risk Budget Gym, Private Markets Harbor, and Rebalancing Dojo. The Quest Board tracks the Topic 3 LOs. Trainers and tall grass now draw Topic 3 MCQs."
 ]},
 {id:'frontierScout', los:['3.1.1b','3.1.2a','3.1.3a'], map:'world4', name:'Efficient Frontier Scout', emoji:'🗺️', c:11, r:5, lines:()=>[
   "Map correction: the efficient frontier is not built for risk-neutral investors. It shows optimal return/standard-deviation combinations for RISK-AVERSE investors.",
   "Another correction: MVO does not optimize returns or risk directly. Returns, risk, covariance, and sometimes higher moments are INPUTS. The optimized OUTPUT is portfolio WEIGHTS.",
   "A concave utility curve — steep at first, then flattening — means declining marginal utility and risk aversion. Linear utility would be risk-neutral."
 ]},
 {id:'factorRanger', los:['3.1.5b','3.1.5c','3.2.4a','3.3.4b'], map:'world4', name:'Factor Lens Ranger', emoji:'🔭', c:13, r:7, lines:()=>[
   "Factor exposure can be estimated with a simple regression: asset return = alpha + beta × factor + residual. Portfolio exposure is the weighted sum of asset betas.",
   "Your factor constraint trap: yes, aggregate beta can be capped below a target beta — but this can be infeasible when short selling is disallowed. Long-only constraints can block the fix.",
   "For TPA factor implementation, use R-E-S-E: set RISK targets, set EXPOSURE targets, set STRATEGY targets, then manage EXECUTION. You missed this twice, so the ranger repeats it twice. R-E-S-E."
 ]},
